# Stopping the backend after use

When the backend is started for checks, tests, API generation, or any other purpose, **always stop the process** when done.

- Do not leave the backend running in the background "just in case".
- After the task is finished (verification, api:gen, debugging, etc.) stop the process explicitly (Ctrl+C in the terminal or kill the process).
- This avoids lingering processes and port conflicts on the next run.
